cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on implementing a parallelized Hamming code decoder on a GPU, which is a form of parallel computing. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the implementation of the decoder on a graphics processing unit, which is a type of hardware architecture. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The Hamming code is a type of error-correcting code used in information theory, and the paper discusses its implementation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the implementation of a real-time software-defined radio system, which falls under the category of systems and control. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the implementation of a wireless communication system, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture.
